---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="Terms and conditions governing the use of Reliable Inspections services and website."
>
  <main class="py-section-md px-page">
    <div class="contained">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-8 md:col-start-3">
          <header class="mb-el-xl">
            <h1 class="text-title-lg mb-el-md font-semibold">
              Terms of Service
            </h1>
            <p class="text-body-md text-dark-1">
              Effective date: January 1, 2025
            </p>
          </header>

          <div
            class="[&_h2]:text-title-sm [&_h2]:text-dark-3 [&_h2]:mb-el-md [&_h2]:mt-el-xl [&_h3]:text-body-lg [&_h3]:text-dark-3 [&_h3]:mb-el-sm [&_h3]:mt-el-lg [&_p]:text-body-md [&_p]:text-dark-1 [&_p]:mb-el-md [&_ul]:pl-el-xl [&_ul]:text-body-md [&_ul]:text-dark-1 [&_ul]:mb-el-md [&_li]:mb-el-sm [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_ul]:list-disc"
          >
            <p>
              By scheduling an inspection or using the Reliable Inspections
              website, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. Please
              read them carefully before engaging our services.
            </p>

            <h2>Scope of Inspection Services</h2>
            <p>
              Reliable Inspections provides visual property inspections in
              accordance with the standards of practice established by
              InterNACHI and the Commonwealth of Kentucky. Our inspections are
              limited to observable conditions at the time of the inspection and
              do not constitute a guarantee, warranty, or insurance policy on
              the property or any of its systems or components.
            </p>
            <p>
              Inspections do not include areas that are inaccessible, concealed,
              or not readily visible. We are not responsible for conditions that
              could not be discovered through reasonable visual inspection.
            </p>

            <h2>Scheduling and Cancellation</h2>
            <p>
              Inspections are confirmed upon receipt of payment or a signed
              inspection agreement. If you need to reschedule, please notify us
              at least 24 hours before your appointment. Cancellations made
              within 24 hours of the scheduled time may be subject to a
              cancellation fee.
            </p>

            <h2>Payment</h2>
            <p>
              Payment is due at or before the time of inspection unless other
              arrangements have been made in writing. We accept major credit
              cards and electronic payments. Inspection reports will be released
              upon receipt of full payment.
            </p>

            <h2>Inspection Report</h2>
            <p>
              Your inspection report is provided for your personal use in
              evaluating the property. It is not intended for use by third
              parties and may not be transferred or relied upon by anyone other
              than the client named in the inspection agreement without our
              express written consent.
            </p>
            <p>
              Reports are delivered digitally within 24 hours of the completed
              inspection. We retain reports for a minimum of five years.
            </p>

            <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>
              In the event of a claim arising from our inspection services, our
              liability is limited to the fee paid for the inspection. We are
              not liable for consequential, incidental, or punitive damages of
              any kind. Any claim must be submitted in writing within one year
              of the inspection date.
            </p>

            <h2>Dispute Resolution</h2>
            <p>
              Any dispute arising out of or related to these terms or our
              services shall first be submitted to non-binding mediation in
              Kentucky. If mediation does not resolve the dispute, the parties
              agree to binding arbitration under the rules of the American
              Arbitration Association. These terms are governed by the laws of
              the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
            </p>

            <h2>Website Use</h2>
            <p>
              The content on this website is provided for informational purposes
              only. You may not reproduce, distribute, or use any content from
              this site without our prior written permission. We reserve the
              right to modify or discontinue any part of the website at any
              time.
            </p>

            <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
            <p>
              We may update these terms from time to time. The effective date at
              the top of this page will reflect the most recent revision.
              Continued use of our services after any changes constitutes your
              acceptance of the updated terms.
            </p>

            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <p>
              For questions about these terms, please contact us at{' '}
              <a
                href="mailto:mike@reliableinspectionsky.com"
                class="text-blue-1 underline underline-offset-2"
              >
                mike@reliableinspectionsky.com
              </a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
